<hr />
<h2>4 · Explain the Code 📖</h2>
<p>Read this working coins-and-score code, then answer the questions about it.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">coins = [pygame.Rect(200, 300, 16, 16), pygame.Rect(420, 180, 16, 16)]
score = 0
font = pygame.font.SysFont(None, 36)

for coin in coins[:]:
    if player.colliderect(coin):
        coins.remove(coin)
        score = score + 1

score_text = font.render(f&quot;점수: {score}&quot;, True, (0, 0, 0))
screen.blit(score_text, (10, 10))
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What kind of data structure holds the coins, and what is each coin?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What does <code>player.colliderect(coin)</code> check, and when is it <code>True</code>?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What two things happen inside the <code>if</code> when a coin is touched?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why does the loop use <code>coins[:]</code> instead of <code>coins</code>?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What is the difference between <code>font.render(...)</code> and <code>screen.blit(...)</code>?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

